description: Welcome to this charming penthouse condominium 1,044SF of living blending modern updates with classic character. This 2 bedroom plus unit is situated on the 3rd floor, with a spacious kitchen, a large island, granite countertops, and new SS appliances. A formal dining room, highlighted by a stain glass window and original built-in hutch, adds to the home's timeless appeal. The bay-front living room is canvased with natural light. The 2nd bedroom is generously sized, featuring double closets for ample storage. The updated full bathroom, with contemporary tile work, completes the interior. Step outside through the kitchen to a private deck that leads to your expansive roof deck—an incredible space for entertaining or unwinding while enjoying breathtaking views of the city skyline and harbor. Hardwood floors run throughout the condo. Located just steps from the Curley Community Center,  L St. beach and the unmatched convenience to East Broadway’s trendy shops, restaurants & nightlife.
